Package: bayesEfron
Type: Package
Title: Fully Bayesian Inference for the Empirical-Bayes Deconvolution Problem
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("JoonHo", "Lee",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    email = "joonho112@users.noreply.github.com",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0006-4019-8703"))
Description: Fits the fully Bayesian Efron log-spline prior for
    meta-analytic deconvolution in univariate random-effects settings with
    heteroscedastic within-study standard errors. The package takes
    study-level effect estimates and standard errors, estimates a continuous
    mixing distribution, and returns posterior summaries for latent site
    effects. CmdStan is invoked through 'cmdstanr' with lazy compilation and
    a two-tier on-disk cache. Supporting utilities cover grid construction,
    input conversion from 'metafor' and tidy data frames, sampler
    diagnostics, posterior plotting, and reproducibility metadata.
